        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">FOX is just <span class="text-white font-medium">3 letters for 13 points</span> — that's 4.3 points per tile, the highest efficiency on this entire list. It hooks onto existing words easily (FOXED, FOXES, FOXY) and fits almost any board position.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips for Animal Words</h2>

      <p>Knowing the words is half the battle. Knowing when and where to play them separates good players from great ones.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Target premium squares with X and Z animals:</span> LYNX, FOX, ZEBRA, and ZEBU all contain tiles worth 8-10 points. Landing the X or Z on a Triple Letter Score turns a good play into a game-changing one — FOX with X on TLS scores 37 points from just 3 tiles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Short animals fit tight boards:</span> FOX (3), HAWK (4), LYNX (4), ZEBU (4), and QUAIL (5) can squeeze into congested late-game positions where longer words simply won't fit. Keep these in your mental toolkit for endgame plays.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hook potential matters:</span> MONKEY → MONKEYS, FOX → FOXED/FOXES/FOXY, HAWK → HAWKS/HAWKED, TURKEY → TURKEYS. Animal words with strong hook potential let you score twice — once for the word, once for the parallel play created by the hook letter.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Save high-value animals for big plays:</span> Don't waste JACKDAW or BUZZARD on a plain row. Hold J, Z, and X tiles for positions that access Double/Triple Word Scores. A 24-point JACKDAW becomes 48 on DWS or 72 on TWS.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
