      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Animals by High-Value Tile</h2>

      <p>Grouping animals by their premium tile helps you instantly recall the right word when you draw that J, K, X, or Z from the bag.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Z Animals (Z = 10pts)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ZYZZYVA (43), BUZZARD (28), GAZELLE (17), ZEBRA (16), ZEBU (15) — the Z tile transforms ordinary animals into powerhouse plays.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">X Animals (X = 8pts)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">FOXHOUND (22), VIXEN (15), LYNX (14), FOX (13) — X animals tend to be short, making them ideal for tight board positions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">J Animals (J = 8pts)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JACKDAW (24), JACKAL (19) — fewer options but both deliver big scores with the 8-point J tile.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">K Animals (K = 5pts)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JACKDAW (24), MACKEREL (16), COCKATOO (16), MONKEY (15), HAWK (14), DONKEY (14), TURKEY (13) — K appears in the most animal words on this list.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Length vs Score Comparison</h2>

      <p>Longer words don't always mean higher scores. This comparison shows how short animal words often outperform their longer counterparts on a per-tile basis.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📏 Short & Deadly (3-5 letters)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">FOX (13pts, 3 letters) = 4.3 pts/tile<br/>HAWK (14pts, 4 letters) = 3.5 pts/tile<br/>ZEBU (15pts, 4 letters) = 3.75 pts/tile<br/>LYNX (14pts, 4 letters) = 3.5 pts/tile<br/>QUAIL (14pts, 5 letters) = 2.8 pts/tile</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📐 Long & Powerful (7+ letters)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ZYZZYVA (43pts, 7 letters) = 6.1 pts/tile<br/>BUZZARD (28pts, 7 letters) = 4.0 pts/tile<br/>JACKDAW (24pts, 7 letters) = 3.4 pts/tile<br/>FOXHOUND (22pts, 8 letters) = 2.75 pts/tile<br/>CASSOWARY (17pts, 9 letters) = 1.9 pts/tile</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">⚠️ Remember</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Playing all 7 tiles earns a <span class="text-white font-medium">50-point bingo bonus</span>. So JACKDAW (24 + 50 = 74 total) and BUZZARD (28 + 50 = 78 total) are worth holding out for if you have 6 of the 7 letters on your rack.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Valid vs Invalid — The Proper Noun Rule</h2>

      <p>Not every animal you can think of works in Scrabble. The dividing line is simple: common nouns (lowercase in a sentence) are valid; proper nouns (capitalised names) are not.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Always Valid</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Generic species: FOX, HAWK, ZEBRA, MONKEY, PYTHON, GIRAFFE, SQUID, TURKEY — common nouns that describe the general animal type.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Never Valid</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Breed names & proper nouns: Labrador, Siamese, Doberman, Persian, Angus, Friesian — these are capitalised names and not allowed in Scrabble.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

